The video game craze has been on a steady rise in the past decade, making it a $100 billion global industry. Nearly two thirds of American families have a family member who plays video games regularly. But, what exactly causes these influx of sales? Perhaps, certain genres or publishers attract audiences more than others. I will be inspecting a video game dataset and try to determine if video game sales can be predicted. The dataset in which I have chosen consists of data from the EU, US, and JP regions. I will solely focus on the US category for this experimentâ€™s sake.
